 class=m><span class=title> Re: Money</span><hr size=1> hmmm... i'm a 40th cleric right now and this is my first char. I was only given a few peices of banded, and a kunzar cloak for free, (all of which i gave away). I rarely sellin EC (and when i try, i never actually sell anything and usually end up giving the items away to friends anyhow). The only items i've bought were from jewlers or from NPC merchants (rubies for jewelers, and some uthork stuff that was cheap when i was lower lvl.<br>
<br>
Right now, my wis is about 207, and all but my Int, and Cha is over 100. Also, i have a decent chunk of mana gear. My stuff is about mid lvl. The only cleric quest armor from the temple of Ro is the bracer. None of the other stuff has wisdom on it. <br>
<br>
I find that you make alot more money if you hunt mobs that drop alot of gems/FS or close weapons/and plat. I hunted DL once (good exp, ok group, easy pulls, very little cash). I hunted FM, good cash when i was lvl 24. I never hunted OT or LOIO. <br>
<br>
You could goto Crystal caverns and hunt geonids (find a partner). You could goto GD and hunt giants, and sell the stuff the drop. there is RM giants (overcamped), lots of places on luclin, some places on the old world that are never camped because they are remote or not really known too much, not sure which. <br>
<br>
Also you're comming up to that level where you could start charging for rezes. Now i'm not fully in favor of doing this since i dont' like paying for ports, nor do i like when people withold sow for no good reason except they don't want to cast it. Although since most of my friends are druids and rangers, i rarely beg for these convienences. Anyway, i usually don't charge for rez, and never ask for a donation. When someone wants a rez, i usually ask them what they did. If they died just because of some freak accident, i won't charge even if they are offering a donation. If someone is being utterly stupid, and died on thier own stupid causes (ie. they are a warrior and try to solo 5 reds on purpose) then i'd charge them for wasting my time. If they don't offer a donation, and died for a stupid reason (and this never happened yet) then i might be inclined to ask for compensation, but i doubt it. And i never charge anyone who is a friend, a passing aqaintence, someone who i remember that did an awsome time in a group ect ect ect (and usually i have a good memory about this). And on the same notion, i refuse to rez anyone who did poorly, or was mean to me or anyone i know, ect ect ect. <br>
<br>
To make a long story short, you can charge for rez's in ya want to.<br>
<br>
hmm.... beyond all dat, i usually pull in about 200-300pp a day of playin for about 2-3 hours if i'm killin stuff. <br>
<br>
anyway i need to get back to work....<br>
<br>
so if you need some advice (this is by no means comprehensive) then shoot me a tell, and i'll try to give ya the run through. <br>
<br>
(btw, i never really have more than 1k on me. It usually burns a hole in my pocket.)<br>
